TopicTitle: Help! This always happens and its either an access violation at 0xc0000005 or 0xc0000000

Articles.Content:
Please don't copy and paste the entire log file into your forum post, as it makes your thread very hard to read. I've put the log file contents into a spoiler block, but in the future, please upload your log to Pastebin, and link to the uploaded paste in your post instead.

Looking at this section of the log: 

Unity Player [version: Unity 4.6.4f1_99f88340878d]

mono.dll caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005)
  in module mono.dll at 001b:10107259. 

Error occurred at 2016-05-29_111232.
C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\common\Kerbal Space Program\KSP.exe, run by Lyric.
80% memory in use.
3327 MB physical memory [645 MB free].
0 MB paging file [0 MB free].
2048 MB user address space [56 MB free].
Write to location 00000000 caused an access violation.

The first line mentions Unity 4.6.4, which indicates you are running an outdated version of KSP, 1.0.5 or earlier. Old KSP versions like 1.0.5 are 32-bit applications, and so can only used a maximum of 3.5Gb of RAM before running out of memory and crashing.

Further down the line, it states that you have 3327 MB physical memory (645 MB free). That is the total physical amount of RAM available on your computer, which is used by both your computer's OS, various background services/programs and KSP.

You're experiencing frequent crashes because quite simply, your oomputer does not have enough RAM to run KSP.

Recommended Solutions:

- Buy more RAM for your computer (or better yet, buy a new computer altogether)

- Update your game to KSP 1.1, and run the 64-bit version KSP_x64.exe instead (the 64-bit version is able to use more RAM)

In addition to this, try running fewer other programs when running KSP, other programs will use memory leaving less for KSP to use, and as you mentioned this is worse with mods as they add to the memory required by KSP.

Adding more memory can help a little depending on the situation, but a 32bit application cannot use more than about 3.5gigs of RAM, but having more RAM available will allow other programs to reside in other areas of memory.

This can be limited however by your operating system, with many 32bit versions of Windows being artificially limited in the amount of memory they will support, see this page for details.

64bit operating systems can support much more memory and 64bit programs such as KSP 1.1+ can access more than 3.5gigs of RAM if it is available.

Thanks, my computer is a very old windows vista dell slim540 32 bit and its really hard to play games. I'm playing on the newest version too. I've begged my dad to at least get me a windows 7 that would actually work sometimes, but he said no. Is there any other way I can reduce the amount of memory that is used?

I also just looked again and I noticed that it's using 80% of my memory, so that means 20% Is used by regular processes, but is there much I can do about it? I love ksp, and it is a really great game, and i want to play it, but like most other games, Its to ram consuming for my computer. I dont really know what to do anymore cause now I cant even use newer versions of minecraft forge.

Well @Lyric, there's a few tricks you can try to make KSP use a little less memory.

If you make a shortcut to the KSP.exe you can modify its properties, it will have a 'Target' box that contains the location of the exe

If you add a space then this line you can make KSP run using a different graphics system.

Quote

-force-glcore

You can also try -force-d3d11

They can result in graphical issues though.

Find a way to make a little money. You can get a refurbished pc with window 7 64 bit for less than $150. It actually is gonna cost less to get a refurbished pc than it would to upgrade your old one, especially when you factor in the cost of your time spent doing it. The windows vista 32 bit pc just isn't going to cut it. Seriously, it's going to take quite a bit of time to hack that old pc into any kind of working condition. If you would have spent that same amount of time cleaning gutters or mowing yards or selling lemonade or stuff like that, you could easily make enough money for a refurbished pc from newegg.
